main event: Four unidentified flying objects were observed over Chicago, Illinois for 20 minutes on September 15, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as round and slightly flat at the edges, thicker in the center, and in the white-gray color range.
The objects were 13 feet in diameter and flew in a trail formation, about 50 feet apart.
No distinctive features, tails, trails, exhaust, or sounds were reported.
The objects were first observed from a 7th floor office window and gradually climbed towards the northwest, fading out over the course of about 1 hour and 30 seconds.
The observer used binoculars to view the objects, which were at about the same level as their 7th floor office.
